content.text:
LSP is built-in. In `opencode.json`:

```json
{
  "lsp": {
    "go": {
      "command": ["gopls"]
    },
    "typescript": {
      "command": ["typescript-language-server", "--stdio"]
    },
    "rust": {
      "command": ["rust-analyzer"]
    },
    "custom": {
      "command": ["my-lsp", "--stdio"],
      "extensions": [".custom"]
    }
  }
}
```

30+ language servers are bundled and auto-download on first use. By default only **diagnostics** are fed to the model (errors/warnings after each edit).

For full code intelligence (go-to-definition, find-references, hover, call hierarchy, etc.), enable the experimental LSP tool:

```bash
export OPENCODE_EXPERIMENTAL_LSP_TOOL=true
```

And in config:
```json
{
  "permission": {
    "lsp": "allow"
  }
}
```

**Caveats from the community:** the model sometimes ignores LSP data and falls back to running `tsc --noEmit` or similar. Custom LSP server configs have also had reliability issues per several open GitHub issues.

Note: the active project is `anomalyco/opencode` (TypeScript/Bun). The original Go version (`opencode-ai/opencode`) is archived — its successor is `charmbracelet/crush`.

